title: At NATO summit, Biden’s caution clashed with calls to draw Ukraine closer
description: Tensions at the Vilnius NATO summit exposed the challenges President Biden faces as allies push plans for Ukraine that some fear risk escalation with Russia.

title: Russia says Wagner has returned tanks, missile systems, weapons, ammo
description: Russia's Defense Ministry said it has received more than 2,000 pieces of equipment, 20,000 small arms and 2,750 tons of ammunition from the mercenary group.

title: Chinese hackers breach State Department email through Microsoft cloud
description: Cyberspies from China exploited a fundamental gap in the Microsoft cloud, enabling them to conduct a targeted hack of unclassified U.S. email accounts.

title: Huw Edwards, BBC’s face of historic events, identified as suspended presenter
description: He faces allegations that he paid for sexually explicit images from a teenager. His wife said he has been hospitalized with mental health issues.

title: Biden, G-7 leaders to announce major security assurances for Ukraine
description: The announcement does not provide the same protections that NATO membership offers, but could bolster Ukraine’s ability to defend itself from attack

title: Southern border ‘eerily quiet’ after policy shift on asylum seekers
description: The Biden administration is allowing tens of thousands of migrants to enter the United States legally each month, while those who don’t follow the rules face ramped-up deportations.

title: Milan Kundera, author of ‘The Unbearable Lightness of Being,’ dies at 94
description: His widely translated novels mixed philosophical speculation with political critique and erotic reverie

title: French Swifties are just as annoyed at Ticketmaster as Americans were
description: Much like Taylor Swift's American fans, French Swifties encountered a Ticketmaster meltdown when they attempted to buy tickets for the Eras Tour.

title: This Burger King ‘burger’ is just a bun and a 20-slice tower of cheese
description: The release of the cheesy offering in Thailand prompted mixed reviews. But is it really a burger?

title: Russia-Ukraine war live updates: Busy second day of NATO summit for Zelensky after Kyiv made to wait for invite
description: The Ukrainian leader is set to meet with President Biden and other leaders a day after he criticized NATO’s lack of a clear timeline for his country’s membership.

title: Israel faces an ongoing constitutional crisis — without a constitution
description: A constitutional crisis emerges as protests erupt over Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's plans to remake the country’s judiciary, a move his opponents say enables dictatorship.

title: Enemies duel with drones as Ukraine faces dug-in Russian forces
description: For months, Russian forces have been digging in, building concrete bunkers and constructing tunnel networks. The result is a painstakingly slow Ukrainian counteroffensive in Zaporizhzhia.

title: The Palestinian Authority, teetering on collapse, is tested in Jenin
description: Israel's military operation in Jenin exposed the weakness of the Palestinian Authority, which many Palestinians view as increasingly irrelevant and out of touch.

title: North Korea, after threats to U.S. military, fires long-range missile
description: The missile was in the air for 74 minutes. The launch comes days after Pyongyang warned of “resolute” consequences for U.S. military activity in the region.
